d not expect my legs to misbehave as they did, when--unbuckled andalone--I blithely stepped out of bed on that first night of recovery.Beastly gravity humiliated me at once: my legs telescoped under me. Thecrash brought in the night nurse, and she helped me back into bed. Afterthat I slept. Never before or since did I sleep more deliciously.

